This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses reinforcement and imitation learning, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses beam search, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions simulation experiments, which could potentially involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) if visual input is used in the translation process.
